<!doctype html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta http-equiv='X-UA-Compatible' content='IE=edge;chrome=1' />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Fallback Project</title>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag 'normalize' %>
    <link href="./stylesheets/main.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" />
    <script type="text/javascript" src="//use.typekit.net/lqb2ptd.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript">try{Typekit.load();}catch(e){}</script>
    <link href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/font-awesome/4.0.3/css/font-awesome.css" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="row welcome drop-shadow">
      <div class="container">
        <section>
          <img src="images/brand-logo.png">
          <p class="welcome-message">Hi! Welcome to my <strong>Fallback Project</strong>. I'll cover how I typically setup new projects in conjunction with <a href="http://modernizr.com/">Modernizr</a> to ensure older browsers get some  love <span class="red">&hearts;</span>.</p>
        </section>

        <div class="row important cf">
          <a href="http://meyerweb.com/eric/tools/css/reset/reset200802.css" target="_blank" class="one-half column">
            <h2>CSS Reset</h2>
            <p>Almost always, I will use a CSS reset at the start of a project. The CSS reset I use is quite aggressive, you can opt to use a normalize instead.</p>
          </a>

          <a href="http://modernizr.com/download/" target="_blank" class="one-half column">
            <h2>Modernizr</h2>
            <p>Mordernizr is a great way to detect what HTML5 and CSS3 features a users browser supports and provide a fallback if necessary.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
      <ul class="fallback-list cf">
        <li class="cf">
          <section>
            <div class="one-half column">
              <h2>@font-face</h2>
              <p>Hello, world!</p>
              <p><span class="tag">CSS3</span></p>
            </div>

            <div class="one-half column">
              <p>
                In the header.php template file,
                look for the <code>&lt;div class="header"&gt;</code>
                section to change the <code>&lt;h1&gt;</code> heading.
              </p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </li>

        <li class="cf">
          <section>
            <div class="one-half column">
              <h2>border-radius</h2>
              <p>What is border radius.</p>
              <p><span class="tag">CSS3</span></p>
            </div>

            <div class="one-half column">
              <p>More Explanation</p>
            </div>
          </section>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.10.2/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <script src="./js/main.js"></script>	
	</body>
</html>

